	<text>
		<body>
			<p>Report of the 1st Secretary of the Legation, <persName ref="#ehri_dr_deVeradaragona_carlo_alberto">Carlo Alberto de Vera
					d’Aragona</persName> to the Italian Ministry of Foreign Affairs.</p>
			<p>Incoming telegram no. 2356 R.</p>
			<p>By courier</p>
			<p>Decoded by: SE – Cleartext</p>
			<p>R. Legation <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Bratislava</placeName> 27.3.42.XX</p>
			<p>Bratislava, 6.4.42.XX</p>
			<p>Copy modified in assigning</p>
			<p>Assigned to A.G.</p>
			<p>A.E.M.</p>
			<p>Re: <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/terezin-terms-keyword-jmp-542" type="subject">Measures against the
				Jews</term></p>
			<p>014 - The new measures against the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> that
				had been announced have all of a sudden seen a drastic implementation. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">Ten thousand Jews</term> in towns and in villages had
				received personal summonses in order to be assembled in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496"
					type="subject">concentration camps</term>.</p>
			<p>Due to the ease with which one may convert to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-771" type="subject"
					>evangelical Church</term> and because many of those summoned were aware that public opinion was mostly opposed to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-342" type="subject">anti-Semitic campaign</term>, and also because <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-852" type="subject">rumour</term> had it that the President of the
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html">Republic</placeName>, Monsignor <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000789">Tiso</persName>, was indirectly opposed to such methods of
				persecution, many Jews did not comply with the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject"
					>orders</term> given by <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000261">Minister Mach</persName> . So
				in the night from 23rd to 24th March patrols formed by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119"
					type="subject">police and Guardsmen</term> who had been joined by <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS men</term> arrived from over the nearby border,
				entered Jewish homes, seized three thousand women aged 18 to 35 years, and carried them swiftly on a lorry to the munitions factory in
				Bratislava and to the internment areas of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3058531/nitra.html">Nitra</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3056508/zilina.html">Žilina</placeName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/723819/presov.html"
					>Prešov</placeName>, etc.</p>
			<p>The Authorities closest to the President are denying or trying to downplay the extent of the events that have clearly shaken the public
				opinion here, although everyone knows that the originator of this undertaking is <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000261">Minister Mach</persName>, Commander of the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-397">Hlinka Guard</orgName>, who is being instigated by elements from
				beyond the border and by others who oppose the President, and who accuses the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> themselves of being responsible for
				everything and deserving of the worst punishments.</p>
			<p>It is well-known that the Minister of Interior, who is entirely subservient to the orders from beyond the Danube, intends to gradually
				carry out the concentration and mass deportation of all the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864"
					type="subject">Israelites</term> of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html">Slovakia</placeName>,
				that is approximately 70 thousand souls, the older ones to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1191"
					>General Governorate of Poland</term> (<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName> area) and
				the younger to Ukrainian locations, to be employed in farm labour and in the Organisation Todt. However, since at least for the time
				being they are mostly women still in the bloom of youth and of good social standing, no doubt their employ will be of an entirely
				different character and purpose, in the train of the German units operating in southern Russia.</p>
			<p>The announcement of harsher anti-Semitic measures had already prompted the Holy See to deliver a note to the Minister of Slovakia,
				Mister Sidor; the persecutions that have since taken place have then given rise to repeated démarches on the part of the Apostolic
				Delegate, Monsignor Burzio, with Prime Minister <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000413"
					>Tuka</persName>. As things now stand, the events described above have caused a rift not yet made public but dangerous between
				Prime Minister <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000413">Tuka</persName> and <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000261">Minister Mach</persName> on the one side and President <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000789">Tiso</persName> on the other. The consequences are easy to
				predict if the anti-Semitic persecution should continue in the manner reported above and the President of the Republic, being a cleric
				and a parish priest with the care of souls, should sooner or later be faced with a serious crisis of conscience.</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_dr_deVeradaragona_carlo_alberto">De Vera</persName></p>
